div.h1: EOI Timing: Why Forgetting EOI Freezes the System

div.p: Rule: An IRQ is only serviced if:
ISR bit stays set until EOI Without EOI, all lower IRQs wait forever
The CPU isn't crashedit's just that the PIC refuses to signal any new interrupts.
The system looks dead but is actually running whatever code was executing when the last interrupt returned.
Master PIC acknowledges ISR bit cleared
All IRQs unblocked Next interrupt handled
Handler returns via iret ISR bit remains set
Keyboard: BLOCKED Timer: BLOCKED All lower IRQs: BLOCKED
